Shanty town fire in Philippines leaves 15,000 homeless
A massive fire swept through crowded shanty town near the docks in Manila, destroying houses and leaving 15,000 people homeless, authorities in the Philippine capital said on Wednesday.
Seven people were injured in a fire that broke out late on Tuesday night in Parola Compound in Tondo, Manila, and raged for 10 hours as it spread rapidly, engulfing more than 1,000 makeshift houses, fire officer Edilberto Cruz told reporters. No fatalities were reported.